1 4–301.
2 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
3 (b) “Assault long gun” means any assault weapon listed under § 5–101(r)(2) of the
4 Public Safety Article.
5 (c) “Assault pistol” means any of the following firearms or a copy regardless of
6 the producer or manufacturer:
7 (1) AA Arms AP–9 semiautomatic pistol;
8 (2) Bushmaster semiautomatic pistol;
9 (3) Claridge HI–TEC semiautomatic pistol;
10 (4) D Max Industries semiautomatic pistol;
11 (5) Encom MK–IV, MP–9, or MP–45 semiautomatic pistol;
12 (6) Heckler and Koch semiautomatic SP–89 pistol;
13 (7) Holmes MP–83 semiautomatic pistol;
14 (8) Ingram MAC 10/11 semiautomatic pistol and variations including the
15 Partisan Avenger and the SWD Cobray;
16 (9) Intratec TEC–9/DC–9 semiautomatic pistol in any centerfire variation;
17 (10) P.A.W.S. type semiautomatic pistol;
18 (11) Skorpion semiautomatic pistol;
19 (12) Spectre double action semiautomatic pistol (Sile, F.I.E., Mitchell);
20 (13) UZI semiautomatic pistol;
21 (14) Weaver Arms semiautomatic Nighthawk pistol; or
22 (15) Wilkinson semiautomatic “Linda” pistol.
23 (d) “Assault weapon” means:
24 (1) an assault long gun;
25 (2) an assault pistol; or

